collections.name: Cartooners: Beyond the Frame
collections.description:
“Cartooners: Beyond the Frame” is a follow-up initiative designed to extend and enrich the original "Cartooners" collection, which focused on preserving iconic styles and characters spanning nearly a century of American animation. This new phase merges historical reverence for classic cartoons with cutting-edge blockchain and NFT technologies, ensuring the authenticity, ownership, and expanded engagement surrounding these cultural artifacts.
Preservation of American Animation: As a continuation of our original “Cartooners” project, “Beyond the Frame” goes further by spotlighting lesser-known eras, experimental studios, and creative fusions from the 1930s to modern times. This sequel collection not only celebrates iconic classics but also champions the critical cause of saving American animation heritage, ensuring these beloved characters and styles endure in a secure, digital format.

collections.name: The World of Wayang
collections.description:
Wayang is a traditional performing art that uses leather puppets as a medium for performance. These puppets are made of buffalo or cow skin carved with intricate details and played by a puppeteer behind a white cloth screen lit by lamps, creating dramatic shadows.

Wayang usually tells epic stories, as well as local stories that contain deep moral and philosophical values. This performance is accompanied by set of traditional music instruments, with puppeteer's narration, songs, and dialogues between characters that bring a magical and profound nuance.

In addition to being entertainment, wayang has spiritual and educational meanings, often used in traditional events, religious celebrations, and art performances. Wayang is really unique and extraordinary artistic and historical value.

collections.name: Monet & Gogh: A Postman's Correspondence

## Monet & Gogh: A Postman's Correspondence

**Where art, technology, and history converge.**

Experience a unique NFT collection merging the genius of **Monet** and **Van Gogh**, reimagined through AI. Inspired by their friendship and the letters of their postman, **Joseph Roulin**, these artworks are more than images – they're *unsent letters*, carrying *unspoken emotions* across time.

**Our Story:**

Imagine Monet and Van Gogh in the 21st century, embracing AI as a new medium. Each piece offers a glimpse into their shared world, a testament to art's power, and a connection to a bygone era – all through Roulin's eyes.

**Discover:**

*   **AI-powered fusion** of Impressionism and Post-Impressionism.
*   **Emotionally resonant** art, exploring timeless themes.
*    A purchase for beauty, a link to buy for feeling

**Join us on this artistic journey.**

collections.name: Right to Know
collections.description:
This NFT is a symbol of resistance against historical manipulation, censorship, and the rewriting of truth. Inspired by real-world cases of document tampering and state-controlled narratives, it serves as a digital statement—an immutable mark of the right to transparency and historical accuracy.

While this NFT itself is off-chain, its purpose is to spread awareness and lead the way to the fully on-chain archive where truth is preserved eternally. By holding this piece, you become part of a movement that questions authority, demands accountability, and challenges the very notion of who gets to control history.
